    <p>Designed for user convenience, the News Container contributes to a positive user experience by providing relevant and timely information at a glance.</p>
</section>


       <!-- Section 3: Main Modules -->
<section>
    <h2>Main Modules</h2>
    <p>The heart of PolyTransport lies in its diverse range of modules, each meticulously crafted to cater to specific needs. These modules play a pivotal role in enhancing the overall functionality and user experience of the application.</p>

    <p>Explore the key modules below:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Bus Information:</strong> Delve into comprehensive details about bus routes, stops, and real-time tracking. Users can access personalized information by providing their enrollment number, ensuring they stay well-informed about schedules and receive timely notifications.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Payment Management:</strong> Seamlessly manage payments for bus services. Users can input their name, class, bus stop, and enrollment details, along with uploading a photo. The "Make Payment" feature initiates a secure payment process, centralizing payment activities and promoting transparency.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>User Feedback:</strong> Prioritize user engagement through a streamlined feedback mechanism. Allow students and staff to share their thoughts, suggestions, and concerns. Regularly address user feedback, demonstrating a commitment to meeting the needs of the college community and ensuring a positive and user-centric bus system.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Driver And Vehicle Information:</strong> Maintain a comprehensive database of experienced and licensed drivers, ensuring safety standards. Keep accurate records of each bus, including maintenance history and relevant specifications. Regularly update and monitor driver and vehicle data to uphold the reliability and safety of the transportation service.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p>These modules collectively contribute to PolyTransport's commitment to providing a seamless, secure, and user-friendly environment for managing college bus information.</p>
</section>

       <!-- Section 4: Pop-up Modals -->
<section>
    <h2>Pop-up Modals</h2>
    <p>Enhancing user interactions, PolyTransport employs intuitive pop-up modals to facilitate specific actions and gather essential information.</p>

    <p>Key features of the pop-up modals:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Enrollment Number Modal:</strong> This modal prompts users to enter their enrollment number. It serves as a gateway for accessing personalized information within various modules. Users simply input their enrollment number, and upon submission, gain access to relevant details such as bus routes, stops, and more.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Module 2 Enrollment Modal:</strong> In the payment management module, a specific modal requires users to enter their enrollment number. This step ensures a secure and streamlined payment process. Users provide their enrollment details, and upon submission, initiate the payment procedure for bus services.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Feedback Form Modal:</strong> PolyTransport values user feedback. The feedback form modal allows students and staff to share their thoughts, suggestions, and concerns effortlessly. The form includes fields for name, class, roll number, feedback, and a rating. Upon submission, this feedback contributes to ongoing improvements in the bus system.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p>These pop-up modals are designed with user convenience in mind, ensuring a seamless and interactive experience throughout the PolyTransport web application.</p>
</section>


